<h1>SlotBot Terms of Service</h1>

<p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 11, 2026</p>

<p>
By using SlotBot ("the Bot"), you agree to these Terms of Service.
If you do not agree with these terms, you should discontinue use of the Bot.
</p>

<h2>Use of the Bot</h2>

<p>
SlotBot provides entertainment, virtual economy, and game-related features through Discord.
The Bot is provided on an "as-is" basis without warranties of any kind.
</p>

<h2>Virtual Currency and Items</h2>

<p>
All currency, balances, points, items, rewards, and other virtual assets provided by SlotBot are fictional and have no real-world monetary value.
They cannot be redeemed, exchanged, sold, or converted into real money, cryptocurrency, gift cards, or any other item of value.
</p>

<h2>User Conduct</h2>

<p>Users agree not to:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Exploit bugs or unintended mechanics.</li>
    <li>Use automation, self-bots, or unauthorized scripts.</li>
    <li>Attempt to disrupt or damage the Bot's operation.</li>
    <li>Abuse, harass, or interfere with other users through the Bot.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Enforcement</h2>

<p>
The Bot owner reserves the right to reset balances, remove virtual assets, restrict access, or remove data from users who violate these Terms.
</p>

<h2>Availability</h2>

<p>
The Bot may be modified, suspended, discontinued, or updated at any time without prior notice.
Availability and uptime are not guaranteed.
</p>

<h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>

<p>
To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Bot owner shall not be liable for any damages, losses, or interruptions arising from the use of SlotBot.
</p>

<h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>

<p>
These Terms may be updated from time to time.
Continued use of the Bot after changes are published constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>

<p>
Questions regarding these Terms may be directed to the Bot owner through Discord.
</p>

